<l>valloṟṟut toṭarmoḻi valleḻuttu varuvaḻit</l>
<l>tollai yiyaṟkai nilaiyalu murittē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The original nature of the ' voiceless stop-sequence word '</l>
<l>may remain as such if the coming word begins with a voiceless</l>
<l>stop.<note
              place="foot">I.e, the overshort <foreign xml:lang="ta">u</foreign> at the end of the <foreign
                xml:lang="ta">valloṟṟuttoṭarmoḻi</foreign> remains when followed by a voiceless
          occlusive, e.g. <foreign xml:lang="ta">kokkuk kaṭitu</foreign> (non-case) or <foreign
                xml:lang="ta">kokkuk kaṭumai</foreign> (case).</note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
